cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it introduces a new layer for neural networks that combines neural networks and tree ensembles. It also proposes a new sparse activation function for sample routing and develops specialized forward and backward propagation algorithms that exploit sparsity. 

It could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category as it proposes a new method for training neural networks that combines differentiable decision trees and neural networks. 

The Computer Vision (cs.CV) category is also a possibility as the paper reports experiments on CIFAR, MNIST, and Fashion MNIST datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category is another possibility as the paper proposes a new method for training neural networks that combines neural networks and tree ensembles. 

Finally, the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category is a possibility as the paper proposes a new sparse activation function for sample routing and develops specialized forward and backward propagation algorithms that exploit sparsity.
